<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-20T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-20T04:00:00-05:00" n="190" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.248/357: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-20T10:00:00+01:00">May 20,
                                    1940—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received May 20—7:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>759. For the President. Please give me answers at the earliest possible
                            moment on following questions in previous telegrams: (1) 54 PB Navy
                            bombers; (2) Mackenzie King—reserve pilots to Canada; (3) 2,000 French
                            75’s; (4) destroyers; (5) Reynaud’s communication which was made orally
                            to me instead of by written note.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>